Antenna (

, 

) relatively slender, subcylindrical joint I densely (especially basomedially), joint II–III sporadically with long erect hairs. Relative length of antennal joints I to IV as 72:20:40:14.

Antennae (

, 

) long, first joint slightly curved, widest in basal fourth, with long, dense pubescence medially, and erect or curled hairs along the entire length. Joint II slightly, evenly widening toward apex, III very slightly curved, subcylindrical, suddenly thickening at apex, IV pyriform. Relative length of antennal joints I to IV as 89:25:58:19.

